Pre-Game Insights: The Faroe Islands and North Macedonia will hope to get a leg up in their efforts to gain promotion from League C this year.
Home advantage should count for something as the Scandinavian hosts look to show some defiance and give their UEFA Nations League hopes an instant boost in the bid for promotion.
Miscellaneous Highlights: This match falls almost exactly 12 months after North Macedonia last recorded a competitive win.
The Faroe Islanders have not collected a meaningful victory since they defeated Turkey 2-1 in the UEFA Nations League two years ago:
Others: The two teams line up in Group 4 of the competition’s third tier and are aiming to climb after each finishing third in their respective pools in the last campaign and failing to progress on that occasion.
It was only last year the two nations met for the first time, with North Macedonia hoping to repeat those friendly heroics after Bojan Miovski’s goal was all that separated the pair.
